getBaselineTemplates

BaselineTemplates getBaselineTemplates()
                                       throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Deprecated. This method is deprecated since the introduction of support for request baseline templates in Dimensions 9.1 as well as item baseline templates; instead of this method, call the method getItemBaselineTemplates.

Returns the collection of item baseline templates defined in the base database. For backward compatibility with Dimensions 8.0, this method just calls getItemBaselineTemplates.

Returns:
the collection of item baseline templates
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs
See Also:
getItemBaselineTemplates()

getItemBaselineTemplates

BaselineTemplates getItemBaselineTemplates()
                                           throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Returns the collection of item baseline templates defined in the base database. Use this collection to add new item baseline templates to the base database.

Note: Baseline templates are defined at a global level and are not associated with a specific product. This product is only used to restrict the list the list of item types when defining a new template or editing the details of an existing one.

Returns:
the collection of item baseline templates
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs
See Also:
getRequestBaselineTemplates()

getTypes

Types getTypes(TypeScope scope)
               throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Returns the collection of registered object types of the specified type scope. The ITEM, REQUEST, BASELINE, DESIGN_PART scopes are valid for all products. The USER scope is valid only for the $GENERIC product. Attempting to obtain the user type collection from any product other than $GENERIC will result in an exception being thrown. The user types collection for the $GENERIC product cannot be modified, and contains only one predefined type. This predefined user type object cannot be modified, and exists only to support the definition of user attributes for Dimensions users.

Parameters:
scope - object type scope.
Returns:
the corresponding collection of object types
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the supplied value of code is unsupported.
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs
See Also:
TypeScope

getUserTypes

Types getUserTypes()
                   throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Returns the collection of registered user types. This collection is valid only for the $GENERIC product. Attempting to obtain the user type collection from any product other than $GENERIC will result in an exception being thrown. The user types collection for the $GENERIC product cannot be modified, and contains only one predefined type. This predefined user type object cannot be modified, and exists only to support the definition of user attributes for Dimensions users.

Returns:
the collection of registered user types.
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException
